# 📄 **TECH PRD — Adaptive Agent Organization (AAO)**

## **Section 1: Overview & Vision (FINAL v3)**

---

## 🧠 1.1 System Overview

The **Adaptive Agent Organization (AAO)** is a distributed, self-evolving multi-agent system built in Go, where autonomous agents collaborate via A2A protocol to solve complex tasks with strict quality enforcement, full traceability, and horizontal scalability.

The system behaves like a **real-world AI organization**, consisting of:

* **CEO Agent** → strategy, hiring, governance
* **Manager Agents** → strict coordination & validation
* **Worker Agents** → execution with enforced self-critique
* **Testing Team** → final validation authority
* **Feedback Analysis Team** → continuous improvement

All agents operate over a shared **Task Graph + Threaded Execution Model**, ensuring visibility, coordination, and accountability.

---

## 🎯 1.2 Vision

To build a system that functions as a:

> 🧠 **Self-evolving, fully observable, horizontally scalable AI organization**

Where:

* Agents can **move across systems (portable intelligence)**
* Work is **distributed across unlimited compute (scalable execution)**
* Every action is **traceable as a graph**
* Every failure becomes **input for improvement**

---

## 🧵 1.3 Threaded Execution Model (Execution Graph)

The system uses a **Thread + Subthread model** to represent all work as a **hierarchical execution graph**.

---

### 🧩 Thread Definition

```go
type Thread struct {
    ThreadID   string
    TaskID     string
    ParentID   *string

    Label      string // CEO / Manager / Team / Worker
    AgentID    string
    TeamName   string

    Status     string
    StartedAt  time.Time
    EndedAt    *time.Time
}
```

---

### 🌳 Execution Graph

```txt
Main Thread (Client Request)
  └── CEO Thread
        └── Manager Thread (Team Alpha)
              ├── Worker Thread (Team Alpha / Worker A)
              ├── Worker Thread (Team Alpha / Worker B)
        └── Manager Thread (Team Beta)
```

---

### 🎯 Purpose

Enables:

✅ Full system observability
✅ Clear ownership tracking
✅ Debuggable execution paths
✅ UI-based graph visualization

---

## 📉 1.4 Feedback & Improvement System

The system includes a **dedicated feedback intelligence layer** to capture and act on failures.

---

### 📌 Feedback Sources

* Client dissatisfaction
* Manager rejection
* Testing failure
* Poor agent output
* Repeated revisions

---

### 📦 Feedback Model

```go
type Feedback struct {
    ID        string
    TaskID    string
    ThreadID  string

    Source    string
    AgentID   string

    Type      string // bug, misalignment, quality_issue

    Message   string
    Rating    int

    CreatedAt time.Time
}
```

---

## 🧠 1.5 Feedback Analysis Team

A dedicated team of agents responsible for:

* Identifying recurring issues
* Detecting weak agents
* Suggesting improvements
* Recommending:

  * retraining
  * replacement
  * new hiring

---

## 🔄 1.6 Continuous Improvement Loop

```txt
Execution → Feedback → Analysis → Improvement → Better Execution
```

---

## ♻️ 1.7 Agent Portability (NEW CRITICAL REQUIREMENT)

Agents must be **fully portable across repositories and environments**.

---

### 🧩 Definition

> Any agent developed in one repository must be **copy-paste deployable** into another repository and start functioning without modification.

---

### ✅ Requirements

* No tight coupling to repo-specific code

* All dependencies must be:

  * contract-based OR
  * A2A-based

* Agent must rely only on:

  * A2A messaging
  * Agent Directory
  * Task Store interfaces

---

### 🚫 Forbidden

* Direct imports across agents
* Hidden dependencies
* Hardcoded paths or services

---

### 🎯 Outcome

```txt
Agents = Plug-and-Play Intelligence Units
```

---

## 📈 1.8 Horizontal Scalability (NEW CRITICAL REQUIREMENT)

The system must support **massive parallel scaling** without conflicts.

---

### 🧩 Scenario

```txt
100 agents × 100 pods = 10,000 running agent instances
```

System must still:

* Route correctly
* Avoid duplication conflicts
* Maintain identity clarity

---

### 🔑 Key Requirements

---

### 1. Logical vs Physical Identity

Each agent has:

```txt
Logical ID  → "blog-writer-agent"
Instance ID → "blog-writer-agent-pod-73"
```

---

### 2. Stateless Execution

Workers must:

* Not depend on local memory
* Fetch state from TaskStore

---

### 3. Task Claiming Mechanism

Workers can pick tasks dynamically:

```txt
Any worker instance → can process any task
```

---

### 4. No Central Bottleneck

* Distributed processing
* Event-driven coordination

---

### 5. Idempotent Operations

Repeated execution must not break system state.

---

### 🎯 Outcome

```txt
System scales horizontally without coordination conflicts
```

---

## 🏢 1.9 Organizational Model

```txt
Client
  ↓
CEO Agent
  ↓
Managers (Strict Enforcers)
  ↓
Workers (Self-Critical Executors)
  ↓
Testing Team (Final Gatekeeper)
  ↓
Feedback Team (Improvement Engine)
```

---

## 🔥 1.10 Key Innovations

---

### ✅ Thread-Based Execution Graph

Full visibility into system behavior

---

### ✅ Self-Critical Workers

Agents must validate their own output multiple times

---

### ✅ Strict Manager Enforcement

No misaligned work is accepted

---

### ✅ Independent Testing Authority

Final validation layer with pass/fail control

---

### ✅ Feedback Intelligence System

Continuous learning from failures

---

### ✅ Dynamic Agent Hiring

System expands capabilities in real-time

---

### ✅ Agent Portability

Agents are reusable across systems

---

### ✅ Horizontal Scalability

System works across thousands of instances

---

## ⚙️ 1.11 System Principles

---

### Principle 1: **Trace Everything**

Every action must map to:

```txt
TaskID + ThreadID
```

---

### Principle 2: **Zero Trust Between Agents**

* All outputs must be validated
* No blind trust

---

### Principle 3: **Continuous Self-Improvement**

* Feedback is mandatory
* Learning is continuous

---

### Principle 4: **Strict Role Enforcement**

* Workers → self-critique
* Managers → strict validation
* Testers → final authority

---

### Principle 5: **Portability by Design**

Agents must work across repositories without modification.

---

### Principle 6: **Scalability by Default**

System must function correctly under massive horizontal scaling.

---

### Principle 7: **CEO as Supreme Controller**

CEO can:

* Inspect any thread
* Intervene anywhere
* Replace or terminate agents
* Override decisions

---

## 🚀 1.12 Expected Outcomes

The system will:

* Provide **graph-based execution visibility**
* Scale across thousands of agent instances
* Allow **plug-and-play agent reuse**
* Continuously improve via feedback loops
* Maintain **strict output quality guarantees**
* Operate as a **self-growing AI organization**

---

## 📌 End of Section 1 (FINAL LOCKED)

